Currently, the form and content

7
00:02:19,860 --> 00:02:21,680
have not been confirmed yet.

8
00:02:21,820 --> 00:02:22,740
If you have any ideas,

9
00:02:22,829 --> 00:02:24,320
feel free to tell me anytime.

10
00:02:24,840 --> 00:02:25,720
Of course,

11
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:27,360
throughout the recording process,

12
00:02:27,440 --> 00:02:29,540
we'll also fully respect your opinions.

13
00:02:33,840 --> 00:02:35,820
-About the...
-How did you know Xia Chu?

14
00:02:44,820 --> 00:02:46,470
We started as Internet friends.

15
00:02:47,770 --> 00:02:48,610
I found an article

16
00:02:48,710 --> 00:02:50,610
she wrote on the Internet

17
00:02:51,470 --> 00:02:52,760
about her first love.

18
00:02:53,420 --> 00:02:54,360
At that time,

19
00:02:54,570 --> 00:02:55,840
I was about to graduate from university.

20
00:02:56,390 --> 00:02:57,890
I couldn't find a job yet.

21
00:02:58,610 --> 00:03:00,390
Quota for postgraduate studies
had all been filled up.

22
00:03:00,650 --> 00:03:01,610
My boyfriend wanted to break up with me.

23
00:03:01,710 --> 00:03:03,090
I was extremely depressed.

24
00:03:03,920 --> 00:03:05,470
But after reading her article,

25
00:03:05,710 --> 00:03:06,660
I was inspired.

26
00:03:06,920 --> 00:03:08,380
I replied to her article.

27
00:03:08,700 --> 00:03:11,640
Then, we started texting
each other on WeChat.

28
00:03:12,710 --> 00:03:14,880
Later on, we arranged a meet-up.

29
00:03:15,150 --> 00:03:16,490
It's kind of weird.

30
00:03:17,070 --> 00:03:18,810
Although our age gap

31
00:03:19,470 --> 00:03:21,180
is quite big

32
00:03:21,630 --> 00:03:23,180
and our personalities are so different,

33
00:03:23,270 --> 00:03:24,290
but somehow we had

34
00:03:24,440 --> 00:03:26,270
endless topics to talk about
every time we meet.

35
00:03:29,760 --> 00:03:31,450
Maybe it's because

36
00:03:31,550 --> 00:03:33,170
we are both brilliant individuals

37
00:03:33,310 --> 00:03:36,840
and role models of outstanding
contemporary young women?

38
00:03:36,960 --> 00:03:39,340
Hence we empathize and admire each other.

39
00:03:40,760 --> 00:03:42,610
Did she ever mention to you about...

40
00:03:43,520 --> 00:03:44,420
You?

41
00:03:44,810 --> 00:03:45,870
Yes.

42
00:03:46,230 --> 00:03:47,110
Me.

43
00:03:47,690 --> 00:03:48,410
Of course she did.

44
00:03:48,510 --> 00:03:49,460
She told me a lot

45
00:03:49,540 --> 00:03:51,170
about your past with her.

46
00:03:51,350 --> 00:03:52,230
What happened after that?

47
00:03:53,050 --> 00:03:55,390
Was she in a new relationship?

48
00:03:55,470 --> 00:03:56,730
She had a relationship
during her university years

49
00:03:57,450 --> 00:03:58,630
but it ended very soon.

50
00:03:59,290 --> 00:04:00,350
She was too busy.

51
00:04:05,330 --> 00:04:06,430
Too busy?

52
00:04:07,470 --> 00:04:09,010
Perhaps it was because she was too busy.

53
00:04:09,550 --> 00:04:11,290
Perhaps it was because of other reasons.

54
00:04:12,170 --> 00:04:13,270
Perhaps it was because of you.

55
00:04:17,250 --> 00:04:18,440
What do you want to know?

56
00:04:23,430 --> 00:04:24,930
<i>Long Yi</i>

57
00:04:25,459 --> 00:04:26,440
Please excuse me.

58
00:04:32,780 --> 00:04:34,280
<i>His name is Liang Mu Ze.</i>

59
00:04:34,470 --> 00:04:35,600
<i>He's from the Special Forces.</i>

60
00:04:36,110 --> 00:04:37,650
<i>Now an army major.</i>

61
00:04:37,760 --> 00:04:39,420
<i>Xia Chu is close to him.</i>

62
00:04:39,930 --> 00:04:42,620
<i>They're living in together now.</i>

63
00:04:42,790 --> 00:04:44,100
I got it.

64
00:04:53,110 --> 00:04:53,950
It's fine.

65
00:04:54,040 --> 00:04:56,170
You should get going if you're busy.
Don't worry about me.

66
00:04:59,780 --> 00:05:01,000
It's him.

67
00:05:08,580 --> 00:05:09,640
It's really him.

68
00:05:10,420 --> 00:05:11,610
Are you okay?

69
00:05:25,080 --> 00:05:28,070
<i>Outpatient Department</i>

70
00:05:25,630 --> 00:05:26,860
Please clear the front.

71
00:05:27,030 --> 00:05:28,330
Make way, please.

72
00:05:29,840 --> 00:05:31,180
Please make way.

73
00:05:34,730 --> 00:05:36,270
I'm sorry. You have to wait outside.

74
00:06:06,040 --> 00:06:06,920
<i>Military and Police Take Down Drug Den</i>

75
00:06:12,150 --> 00:06:14,400
Cheers to our final night together.

76
00:06:20,380 --> 00:06:22,160
Is everyone ready?

77
00:06:22,420 --> 00:06:24,300
This is the final test
of this military training program,

78
00:06:24,430 --> 00:06:26,050
namely the endurance test.

79
00:06:26,540 --> 00:06:29,040
It's the ultimate test of your willpower.

80
00:06:29,370 --> 00:06:32,060
As soon as someone touches the tear gas,

81
00:06:32,260 --> 00:06:33,720
I'll start the timer.

82
00:06:34,490 --> 00:06:37,240
The test ends when each individual
leaves this room

83
00:06:37,330 --> 00:06:38,990
and marks will be added
into your final scores.

84
00:06:40,390 --> 00:06:41,400
In other words,

85
00:06:41,490 --> 00:06:42,990
as long as you stay
in this room long enough,

86
00:06:43,180 --> 00:06:45,030
you can still catch up with the scores
although you were behind?

87
00:06:45,320 --> 00:06:46,030
That's right.

88
00:06:46,150 --> 00:06:47,630
Good luck to everyone.

89
00:06:47,720 --> 00:06:49,530
It's going to be a tough one today.

90
00:06:50,100 --> 00:06:51,180
Liang Mu Ze.

91
00:06:51,310 --> 00:06:52,580
You'll put the tear gas

92
00:06:52,710 --> 00:06:54,220
-into the pot.
-Okay.

93
00:06:56,159 --> 00:06:57,340
Let's make a deal first.

94
00:06:57,710 --> 00:06:58,980
Whoever leaves this room first

95
00:06:59,070 --> 00:06:59,940
will buy everyone a meal.

96
00:07:00,020 --> 00:07:01,810
-Sure.
-No problem.

97
00:07:03,370 --> 00:07:04,440
Liang Mu Ze.

98
00:07:04,909 --> 00:07:06,720
How could you start
without telling us first?

99
00:07:07,910 --> 00:07:09,250
I'm going all out.

100
00:07:14,030 --> 00:07:15,060
I really want to know

101
00:07:15,150 --> 00:07:16,060
if you were ever defeated before

102
00:07:16,150 --> 00:07:18,010
all these years in the force.

103
00:07:18,500 --> 00:07:20,040
Of course he was.

104
00:07:20,260 --> 00:07:22,530
I'll take him down today.

105
00:07:23,260 --> 00:07:24,310
I want to know

106
00:07:25,350 --> 00:07:26,760
who that legend is.

107
00:07:27,150 --> 00:07:28,370
I must meet him.

108
00:07:30,790 --> 00:07:31,890
You can't meet him anymore.

109
00:07:34,040 --> 00:07:35,160
He died in service.

110
00:07:37,390 --> 00:07:38,130
If it wasn't for him,

111
00:07:38,220 --> 00:07:39,390
I wouldn't be sitting here alive today.

112
00:09:36,180 --> 00:09:37,390
This is wrong.

113
00:09:38,550 --> 00:09:39,500
What did you say?

114
00:09:39,950 --> 00:09:41,210
You should walk ahead of me.

115
00:09:43,400 --> 00:09:44,620
Is there a difference?

116
00:09:45,870 --> 00:09:48,850
It'll be the right direction
when you walk ahead of me.

117
00:09:50,300 --> 00:09:52,280
Following you keeps me steady.

118
00:09:53,290 --> 00:09:55,670
It has been eight years, Mu Ze.

119
00:09:56,770 --> 00:09:58,780
You don't have to walk in my footsteps.

120
00:09:59,100 --> 00:10:00,000
I need to.

121
00:10:01,940 --> 00:10:03,120
To others,

122
00:10:03,860 --> 00:10:05,960
many things may change in eight years.

123
00:10:06,950 --> 00:10:08,220
But to me,

124
00:10:10,580 --> 00:10:11,880
you'll always be my captain.

125
00:11:21,050 --> 00:11:22,320
The patient is experiencing
ventricular tachycardia.

126
00:11:22,430 --> 00:11:23,100
Get the defibrillator.

127
00:11:23,190 --> 00:11:24,690
IV infusion, 100 mg of lidocaine.

128
00:11:33,420 --> 00:11:34,520
Heart rate is back to normal.

129
00:12:35,140 --> 00:12:38,530
Why did you drink so much today?

130
00:12:38,690 --> 00:12:40,900
Don't you have to
return to the force tomorrow?

131
00:12:42,610 --> 00:12:44,550
Stop drinking. It's bad for your stomach.

132
00:12:47,080 --> 00:12:48,570
Tomorrow is an off day.

133
00:12:51,100 --> 00:12:52,240
You cried?

134
00:12:53,170 --> 00:12:54,270
Tear gas.

135
00:13:00,590 --> 00:13:01,600
My head hurts.

136
00:13:02,260 --> 00:13:04,410
I'll make you honey drink to sober up.

137
00:13:21,240 --> 00:13:22,860
Sit down and talk with me.

138
00:13:36,350 --> 00:13:38,170
Today is the anniversary of

139
00:13:39,150 --> 00:13:40,050
Luo Liang's death.

140
00:13:40,840 --> 00:13:41,820
Luo Liang?

141
00:13:41,940 --> 00:13:42,870
Yes.

142
00:13:44,340 --> 00:13:45,560
Xiao Jun's father.

143
00:13:47,420 --> 00:13:48,730
You were right.

144
00:13:49,800 --> 00:13:51,030
Eight years have passed.

145
00:13:53,590 --> 00:13:55,080
But I still think he is here.

146
00:13:56,430 --> 00:13:57,650
He is still by my side

147
00:13:58,070 --> 00:13:59,410
and in my life.

148
00:14:00,850 --> 00:14:02,590
Sometimes when I'm in my dreams

149
00:14:04,190 --> 00:14:05,770
or when I had too much to drink,

150
00:14:06,620 --> 00:14:07,920
I'll want to talk to him.

151
00:14:13,370 --> 00:14:15,180
I can't believe and accept the fact that

152
00:14:16,830 --> 00:14:18,060
he has totally disappeared

153
00:14:18,150 --> 00:14:19,530
from my life.

154
00:14:19,750 --> 00:14:20,770
I can't accept it.

155
00:14:32,590 --> 00:14:33,810
<i>Luo Liang and I</i>

156
00:14:34,140 --> 00:14:36,330
<i>majored in Special Forces
Military Training.</i>

157
00:14:37,390 --> 00:14:39,850
<i>We joined the Special Forces Brigade
after we graduated.</i>

158
00:14:40,310 --> 00:14:42,890
<i>Like our Brigade Captain Dong Zhi Gang
always said,</i>

159
00:14:42,990 --> 00:14:44,510
<i>"When two similar sharp edges</i>

160
00:14:44,590 --> 00:14:46,170
<i>with the same shine meet,</i>

161
00:14:47,150 --> 00:14:48,330
<i>sparks will fly</i>

162
00:14:48,470 --> 00:14:50,690
<i>when they collide."</i>

163
00:14:51,190 --> 00:14:52,650
<i>We graduated the same year,</i>

164
00:14:53,030 --> 00:14:54,610
<i>served under the same force,</i>

165
00:14:55,070 --> 00:14:56,650
<i>and became platoon sergeants.</i>

166
00:14:57,420 --> 00:14:58,760
<i>Everything was a competition between us.</i>

167
00:14:59,850 --> 00:15:02,070
<i>We competed in our trainings</i>

168
00:15:02,610 --> 00:15:04,430
<i>and shooting skills.</i>

169
00:15:05,400 --> 00:15:06,500
Start!

170
00:15:16,270 --> 00:15:19,660
-Beat him!
-You can do it!

171
00:15:19,750 --> 00:15:21,270
<i>Even in the activity room
during break time,</i>

172
00:15:21,350 --> 00:15:23,100
<i>we competed in</i>

173
00:15:23,190 --> 00:15:25,410
<i>arm wrestling.</i>

174
00:15:26,230 --> 00:15:28,420
You can do it!

175
00:15:28,500 --> 00:15:31,010
You can do it!

176
00:15:31,270 --> 00:15:32,730
<i>Those were the days in the force.</i>

177
00:15:33,190 --> 00:15:34,690
<i>Everything was a competition.</i>

178
00:15:35,330 --> 00:15:36,560
<i>There must be a winner
and loser in everything.</i>

179
00:15:36,720 --> 00:15:38,850
<i>Everyone gave his very best.</i>

180
00:15:39,930 --> 00:15:42,630
Being passionate in everything
was the law of survival in the force.

181
00:15:44,270 --> 00:15:45,770
It was also a special way of expressing

182
00:15:46,300 --> 00:15:48,400
the friendship between Luo Liang and me.

183
00:15:50,670 --> 00:15:51,850
At that time, comrades in the force

184
00:15:51,940 --> 00:15:53,090
would call us

185
00:15:54,670 --> 00:15:57,720
military elites who are equally matched.

186
00:15:58,670 --> 00:15:59,810
When we were

187
00:16:01,030 --> 00:16:02,650
at the peak of our competition,

188
00:16:05,150 --> 00:16:06,390
the force wanted to form

189
00:16:06,470 --> 00:16:08,050
a younger special operations force.

190
00:16:08,670 --> 00:16:10,420
All the young officers
in the special force

191
00:16:10,510 --> 00:16:11,930
signed up for the position

192
00:16:12,350 --> 00:16:13,570
of captain.

193
00:16:14,750 --> 00:16:16,610
<i>After many rounds of tests,</i>

194
00:16:16,770 --> 00:16:18,270
<i>it was down to Luo Liang</i>

195
00:16:18,920 --> 00:16:19,970
<i>and me.</i>

196
00:16:20,400 --> 00:16:21,380
<i>How did it go?</i>

197
00:16:21,470 --> 00:16:22,690
<i>I lost to him.</i>

198
00:16:25,040 --> 00:16:26,430
Why didn't you attend

199
00:16:26,520 --> 00:16:27,580
our first training this afternoon?

200
00:16:28,170 --> 00:16:29,630
I was tired so I didn't want to go.

201
00:16:35,440 --> 00:16:38,180
No matter how tired you are,
you're still the lieutenant.

202
00:16:38,590 --> 00:16:40,730
Bond with the team and train warriors.

203
00:16:40,950 --> 00:16:43,020
The entire brigade is watching us now.

204
00:16:43,180 --> 00:16:45,810
No matter how tired you are,
you have to endure it.

205
00:16:46,140 --> 00:16:47,950
In that case, I'll withdraw
from Team Thunder tomorrow.

206
00:16:48,240 --> 00:16:49,930
I don't care who becomes the lieutenant.

207
00:16:53,030 --> 00:16:54,440
Now that I'm Team Thunder's captain,

208
00:16:55,310 --> 00:16:56,530
you are dissatisfied?

209
00:16:58,700 --> 00:16:59,800
Answer me.

210
00:17:00,040 --> 00:17:02,110
Yes, I am.

211
00:17:02,200 --> 00:17:04,010
Didn't you see the test results?

212
00:17:04,900 --> 00:17:06,000
What makes you captain? Tell me.

213
00:17:06,110 --> 00:17:06,990
What makes you?

214
00:17:09,290 --> 00:17:11,030
The way you're behaving now
says that I'm more worthy.

215
00:17:12,510 --> 00:17:14,490
You're not fit to be
captain of Team Thunder.

216
00:17:15,130 --> 00:17:16,859
You don't even have the basic qualities

217
00:17:16,960 --> 00:17:18,050
of a soldier.

218
00:17:18,150 --> 00:17:19,250
Shut up.

219
00:17:19,710 --> 00:17:21,280
I don't need a lecture from you.
Get lost.

220
00:17:23,190 --> 00:17:24,359
As a soldier,

221
00:17:25,390 --> 00:17:26,819
you rise from where you fall

222
00:17:26,900 --> 00:17:28,440
on the battlefield.

223
00:17:29,400 --> 00:17:31,410
Taking things personal like this,

224
00:17:31,500 --> 00:17:33,720
giving others your attitude
and giving up on yourself

225
00:17:34,270 --> 00:17:35,210
make you a coward.

226
00:17:57,630 --> 00:17:58,650
Do you feel better now?

227
00:17:58,910 --> 00:18:00,250
Get up. Let's continue.

228
00:18:03,270 --> 00:18:04,150
No.

229
00:18:05,150 --> 00:18:06,770
You've already wasted a lot of energy
punching the sand bag today.

230
00:18:06,880 --> 00:18:09,770
If we continue to fight,
I won't win fairly.

231
00:18:10,470 --> 00:18:11,610
How are you so sure that you'll win?

232
00:18:12,680 --> 00:18:14,590
We'll become rivals for a lifetime,
won't we?

233
00:18:16,420 --> 00:18:17,370
There's still a long way to go.

234
00:18:17,910 --> 00:18:19,770
We don't have to do this now.

235
00:18:22,060 --> 00:18:23,400
The Brigade Captain told me that

236
00:18:24,220 --> 00:18:25,730
you're a good sword.

237
00:18:26,390 --> 00:18:27,810
But you still need to be sharpened.

238
00:18:28,590 --> 00:18:30,570
It might do you good

239
00:18:31,590 --> 00:18:33,130
that you're not captain.

240
00:18:34,780 --> 00:18:35,890
Tomorrow morning at nine o'clock,

241
00:18:36,070 --> 00:18:37,900
gather for indoor close-quarters combat.

242
00:18:38,030 --> 00:18:39,840
I'm busy. You can proceed without me.

243
00:18:40,230 --> 00:18:41,420
Don't you dare.

244
00:18:49,070 --> 00:18:49,950
Sir.

245
00:18:50,190 --> 00:18:51,430
Lieutenant of Team Thunder,

246
00:18:51,510 --> 00:18:53,570
code name Whale, requests to return.

247
00:18:54,020 --> 00:18:54,920
Fall in.

248
00:18:58,970 --> 00:19:00,190
From today onwards,

249
00:19:01,180 --> 00:19:02,370
not a single soldier here

250
00:19:03,060 --> 00:19:04,400
will be left behind.

251
00:19:04,910 --> 00:19:05,970
Do you hear me?

252
00:19:06,070 --> 00:19:09,000
Only death will keep us apart.

253
00:19:14,830 --> 00:19:16,260
Xiao Jun's mother said

254
00:19:16,920 --> 00:19:19,540
you went on a mission together.

255
00:19:20,770 --> 00:19:21,870
Yes.

256
00:19:23,950 --> 00:19:25,290
We went on a mission together

257
00:19:30,300 --> 00:19:31,430
but he didn't return.

258
00:19:35,430 --> 00:19:36,690
He was the only one who didn't return.

259
00:19:54,830 --> 00:19:55,810
As usual,

260
00:19:56,280 --> 00:19:58,650
write your will and
the receiver's address.

261
00:19:58,870 --> 00:20:00,290
Submit it before you disembark.

262
00:20:14,110 --> 00:20:15,920
Captain, aren't you going to write one?

263
00:20:16,070 --> 00:20:18,930
Meng Zhen doesn't want to do it. She said
she'll be waiting for me to go home.

264
00:20:20,230 --> 00:20:21,290
Is she going to deliver soon?

265
00:20:21,910 --> 00:20:23,290
One more month to go.

266
00:20:25,060 --> 00:20:27,010
If I don't make it back,

267
00:20:27,550 --> 00:20:28,580
you guys have to look after

268
00:20:28,670 --> 00:20:30,410
the baby and her for me.

269
00:20:30,630 --> 00:20:31,350
Don't worry.

270
00:20:31,430 --> 00:20:33,450
Your son is also my son.

271
00:20:34,590 --> 00:20:35,840
In your dreams!

272
00:20:36,250 --> 00:20:37,950
Your parents are also my parents.

273
00:20:38,150 --> 00:20:40,050
Your pet is also my pet.

274
00:20:41,550 --> 00:20:43,050
Do you remember that poem we recited

275
